i've been to so many places that butcher modern indian/indian fusion cuisine but veda did it right!! only ordered off the sips menu and got the lamb doughnut, goat cheese naan, samosa chaat, and goan crab cakes. 

the goat cheese naan was insane absolutely recommend. goan crab cake was also really good! samosa chaat was ok and i wish the lamb doughnut was just a tad spicier but overall food was good. 

loved the rupee beer!! have been wanting to try it forever and was so glad it's part of their sips menu. bartender was super nice and happy to give us his recommendations for food 

it got very crowded very quickly. definitely head over a little earlier than happy hour if you'd like to sit at the bar!

Our server Nikki was very very helpful and polite. So full marks for her.
Two things. 1) people working in restaurants- be it server or bus persons should NEVER have long hair open.

2) this place needs thorough cleaning and maintenance.
Every chandelier had 2/3rd bulbs missing. Floor was atrocious dirty. 
Chairs stacked on the side. No decorum at all.
One mirror had indian diwali stickers eith half beads missing
Now the food- 
Lassi was thick enough to be called a milkshake.  Lassi is supposed to be thin so we kept adding water 

Appetizers : 

Hummus platter was below average. With bharta served as baba ganoush and crispy roasted chickpeas and the Nan bread was akin to wood chips. Tough and old.

Chicken murmure was passable. Chutneys should immediately withdrawn cause green chutney was frozen & thawed and not even stirred.

Entrées:
Chicken makhani was good .
Chicken thaali was really mediocre
Fish moilee was really good.
Kashmiri Nan was good too

Masala chai was ok 
All in all not returning again

We hosted a brunch before my brother-in-law's wedding. Kiran and the Veda staff were very accommodating and easy to work with weeks leading up to our event. The vibe of the restaurant is very fun and the layout is spacious. It's great for guest of all ages. All the food was amazing and came out quickly and hot. Our guest were very happy! The service was also amazing and attentive. We would highly recommend using Veda to host any sort of event.

Kiran, thank you for your help planning such a fun, relaxing, and tasty pre-wedding brunch 5/5!

Came here for restaurant week and was not disappointed! The makhani curry was insane (honestly could just drink a bowl of it) and the lassoni gobi was super crispy and tasty. The other dishes we got were also great compared to other Indian restaurants I've gone to. Easily one of the best Indian restaurants in Philly. I got a table for two for Saturday lunch with no wait. Comes with free rice and roti or naan. Really good value for $20 per person. Very friendly and quick service. Clean interior and fun vibe.

Great discovery of a modern, fine dining Indian restaurant in the heart of Philadelphia. 
Very warm, inviting and comfortable vibe here. The staff are very attentive, and friendly. 
Unfortunately I wasn't able to explore many items on the menu. I just had a few delicious appetisers. I must say, you have to try the Lasooni Gobi -  which is a lightly battered and flash-fried Cauliflower tossed in a Ginger-Garlic sauce. This was amazing! I'm looking forward to coming back to explore additional items on the very enticing menu. 
Veda sells a beer call Rupee.  It's a  Indian beer carefully made to pair very well with curry. I'm not a beer drinker per se, but I found the taste and overall balance very good. I also had their Old Fashioned, named Old Fashioned Gabor. It consists of wild turkey whiskey, orange liqueur, bitters and turbinado sugar. This was so good!! I should've had another! 

Check Veda out!  It's a delight!

Great food, drinks, service, and ambiance!

We are so glad that we finally made it into Veda. There was a time before the pandemic where we worked out nearby at RowZone and always wanted to go, but we were never in the position to go (well, we could have, but we don't think it would have been too kind to go in there a sweaty, gross mess while others were enjoying a great meal).

The space is great with a large bar with ample seating. We are bar sitters when it's just the two of us, and really enjoyed the exceptional drinks and service during a Yelp event, so we couldn't help but stay for dinner. And we are certainly glad that we did! 

I'm a sucker for a good tandoori chicken and they delivered here. It was very moist, and was the perfect potion size if you ask me. Their naan was some of the best I have ever had, too. My husband got the lamb vindaloo and it too was delicious and a perfect size. They nailed their spice levels - I got a three and he got a four. Sometimes when restaurants ask, I often feel like I end up with the opposite of what I ordered which wasn't the case here. 

Like I noted, service is great. That coupled with the vibe and delicious food will certainly have us coming back very soon!

Recently stopped in to Veda for Happy Hour. Let me just say I love that they have HH everyday AND it lasts til 7, unlike most spots in the city. The restaurant is very pretty, and I loved the chic automatic doors at the entrance. We sat at a high top table (HH is only by the bar) and ordered a variety of items that were all good and priced under $9 each, minus the Chicken Mahkhani which we ordered off the main menu. The service was fine, but don't make the same mistake I did by ordering anything before 5. Even though it was only a few minutes beforehand, I was charged full price for a drink and not the HH price because they use a handheld system that has a timestamp on it. Noted for next time.

Made it out to the city to try more of a modern style Indian restaurant. Beautiful place, from the interior, to the decor, very nice. From walking in to see the hostess, and the server, everyone was just great. 

Now to drinks, love the uniqueness of the cocktails. Not your typical that's for sure. The 3 drinks pictured were the Drunken Lassi, Punjabi Sour, and Boozy Chai. Last one was the happy ending espresso martini so I won't fall into food coma 

Then the food, Tandoori grilled salad, Fish peri-peri, Goan crab cake, Chicken Lababdar and lamb vindaloo. Everything was good, perfect portions, not too much not too little.

I might be really picky about my Indian food (understandably) so my ratings aren't going to be really high for this place. I went here for a friend's baby shower. I really liked the space. They have a great sized bar and a good amount of dine in space as well. The back had a buffet style for this event. I really liked the Indian graphic designed wall. The service was excellent...the wait staff are amazing and really hustled. The buffet was ok. I like my Indian food spicy but definitely this place is Americanized. I really have to say though this place had two stand out dishes- crispy spinach chaat and the kulfi with blueberries. The kulfi was the best I have ever had. I haven't heard of blueberries on top before so it was definitely an interesting twist. The spinach chaat was interesting because I've never had or heard of this dish until I went to this place.

Such a cuteee restaurant with the tastiest apps and nicest staff. They have happy hr 7days a week which is around the time I visited. The ambiance is warm and pretty. It's perfect for a date night or smaller groups. The menu is extensive and the bar is full. Dress code is definitely a bit of everything, but a bit nicer than it is casual. They somehow made cauliflower taste better than chicken and I eat all the meats. Also check out the Rupee beer, it's the perfect light drink to pair with the different rich flavours of food.

Decent modern Indian cuisine! Came here Saturday for lunch during restaurant week's $25 set menus. The vibes were a casual classy, a good place for a date (although the tables were abnormally long) 

We ordered the mussel tikka masala and chicken mirch masala to start. Both apps were small but really yummy, and u thought the mussel fish was very unique. Had a sweet, rich curry. The chicken was wonderfully tender (the first dish came out a little cold but the waitress brought us a new dish right away that was hot). For mains we ordered the bhindi masala and goat rogan josh, which came with rice and our choice of garlic naan and roti. The bhindi was decent, but I wish I had something in a curry instead with my naan so it wasn't as dry. The goat had good flavor but the meat wasn't as tender as the chicken was. For dessert we ordered the gulab jaman and ice cream. The portions were small but both tasted delicious. 

Overall a good spot for restaurant week if you want to try and variety of dishes, but just beware that the portions aren't as big and it might be more worth your money to come with a large group of friends and just order many plates instead.

Veda gets 5 stars for offering Happy Hour 7 days a week from 5 to 7 p.m.

I have not gone here for a meal (brunch, lunch or dinner) since before the pandemic as I have other Indian favorites, namely Amma and Thanal Tavern, that I feel give me much tastier and less expensive dining choices, even if their ambiance is not as spiffy as Veda's.

Veda's interior decoration IS nicely eye catching, which makes an ideal setting for taking up a bit of bar space with a book, a periodical and one of their HH libations. My favorite is the Maharajah Tonic. It's simple, classic, cold and reliably strong. A friend who sometimes joins me for this civilized bargain break between day's end and dinner enjoys the Old Fashioned Gabbar but I find it too cloying. If you like a sweet tipple, go for that one. My second choice, not at the "nice price," is their Manhattan. It's my favorite alcoholic drink for 8 months out of the year and the skilled bartenders here always craft a good one. Unlike some happy hour offerings, where you wonder if a bottle of booze was ever even in the vicinity of your glass (looking at you, Double Knot), you are assured a tasty adult strength drink here. 

Warning: should you order the Drunken Lassi (not on the happy hour menu), it packs a stealth wallop so be moderate, as it's more-ish, dessert sweet, delicious as sin and goes down fast and easy.

If you are sober or sober curious, Veda has some reasonably priced mocktails as well as some non-alcoholic canned beers as part of their bar program. 

My happy hour food go tos are the tandoori grilled salad and the samosa chaat. if I'm feeling flush and expansive, I order the crispy spinach chaat from the dinner menu. It's a few dollars more than what's listed for happy hour, but it's such a marvelous complement to Veda's version of a gin and tonic, I don't begrudge myself the extra $2 for this treat. I also appreciate the fact that if I do order this, the helpful folks serving me alert me to the fact the dish will not be rung up at a happy hour price. Love transparency when eating and drinking somewhere.

The current bartenders here are marvelously adept at sussing out if a patron wants to chat or be left alone which has afforded me both a few hours of pleasant, solitary, slightly snockered reading and eating as well as some lively, humourous conversations. I tip generously for both experiences and their wisdom to know the difference.

Great meal with great ambiance. It feels very classy and clean dining experience. There is much more limited seating space. I was there for restaurant week and the food was so delicious.

Appetizers were just addictive we polished it all. The crispy spinach and okra were both very crispy and savory it was satisfying. The 2nd course the samosa and Mango short ribs were the star. Everything was very good but the samosa in my opinion was delicious with the sauce on the outside, it was perfect. 

The dinner we had 3 curries. Shrimp moilee, lamb rogan josh, and maybe the goat but I don't remember as well but I do know the shrimp moilee is hands down the best. It was so good I almost licked the bowl clean.

By dessert we were about to implode. The sorbet was very very good and so was the ras malai. It was creamy and sweet. The gulab was good but the only problem was it was too too sweet for me.

Overall a great dining experience.

Never disappointed when we come here!  Food is always tasty and flavorful, service usually attentive. 

This time we had the goat cheese Naan, cauliflower (lasooni gobi) and lamb Rogan Josh.   All was delicious but by far the best bite was lasooni gobi.

We arrived for lunch,  without a reservation; it was so busy I guess we were lucky we had seating.   Love the ambience and energy. 

We will definitely return.

I returned to try veda and it was a unique experience - i wished they worked on their craft because I see potential but poor execution 

Okra 3/5
Samosa 2.5/5
Butternut squash soup - 0/5 - inedible
Cauliflower app 1/5 - inedible 
Malai kofta - 3/5
Paneer makhani - 2/5 - very very few paneer pieces
Naan - 0/5 - they don't know how to make naan 
Veggie biryani - 2.5/5 - it could easily become 4 with more veggies and masala but they put a ton of potatoes instead

Been meaning to try this place and it didn't disappoint! The restaurant itself is very spacious and has a full bar. They have specialty cocktails which are basically an Indian twist to certain cocktails. We ordered the butternut squash soup which was super creamy and the spinach chaat for apps. Absolutely loved the spinach chaat. Entree was the chicken lababdar which was full of flavor. Service was very attentive and the server explained the menu and answered any questions we had.

The décor is very colorful and warm, a total amazement compared to what it looks like on the outside. I love that the bathroom sink is leveled nice and high for tall people. My waiter was very chill along with those who assisted him. 

My chicken dish was good but I didn't taste much of the spices in the broth like I did in the lamb. The corn soup definitely has a kick so be ready lol. I llooovveeed the crispy spinach dish, it's a MUST try! If you're going to get bread I'd go for the naan not the roti bc of the dryness. I'll definitely be back there again!

We went to try their the Fall restaurant week menus for dinner. It was a mix of American & Indian food so was good for people who is first time to try Indian food! I really liked how they cooked their chicken & shrimp; it was really juicy and tender. Their authentic Indian dessert "Gulab Jamun" with vanilla ice cream was really sweet, but it has that unique herbal flavor, which will make you think you're in India! The service and vibe were pleasant; highly recommend for brunch or dinner date!

Downgraded to 1 star.

We ordered the food at 8:00 PM today and as of 9:43 PM we are still waiting for it. Uber eats have changed 3 drivers in the meantime because Veda is not ready with the food. Apparently they are still "wrapping it up". 

Tried calling the restaurant maybe 5 times and as usual went to voicemail.

Horrible and unreliable for take out or delivery. I came here to write a 1 star review for this exact reason, read my first review and was shocked to recall that I had literally the same experience with delivery a few years back!!! 

I think I have learnt my lesson and I am never going to order for delivery/takeout again from Veda.

This place was really cool! I came for the restaurant week deal, and they did not disappoint. It's a modern, upscale Indian restaurant with a lot of cool takes on some traditional Indian food, which I generally love. It's a bit pricey for what you get, but all of the food that we had was great. I would probably come here again.

Great food, drinks, service, and ambiance!

We are so glad that we finally made it into Veda. There was a time before the pandemic where we worked out nearby at RowZone and always wanted to go, but we were never in the position to go (well, we could have, but we don't think it would have been too kind to go in there a sweaty, gross mess while others were enjoying a great meal).

The space is great with a large bar with ample seating. We are bar sitters when it's just the two of us, and really enjoyed the exceptional drinks and service during a Yelp event, so we couldn't help but stay for dinner. And we are certainly glad that we did! 

I'm a sucker for a good tandoori chicken and they delivered here. It was very moist, and was the perfect potion size if you ask me. Their naan was some of the best I have ever had, too. My husband got the lamb vindaloo and it too was delicious and a perfect size. They nailed their spice levels - I got a three and he got a four. Sometimes when restaurants ask, I often feel like I end up with the opposite of what I ordered which wasn't the case here. 

Like I noted, service is great. That coupled with the vibe and delicious food will certainly have us coming back very soon!

$ROOT_QUERY.business({\"encid\":\"qBwOLb.full: Recently stopped in to Veda for Happy Hour. Let me just say I love that they have HH everyday AND it lasts til 7, unlike most spots in the city. The spinach chaat was interesting because I've never had or heard of this dish until I went to this place.
